: A wide range of information on higher education courses and career options will be provided to students at a career counselling programme organised by GITAM University, in association with The Hindu School Edition, at St. Michaelâ€™s Girls Higher Secondary School at West Hill in Kozhikode on January 20 (Wednesday).The programme will begin at 1.30 p.m.Guidance on coursesIntermediate students will be guided on choosing professional and general higher education courses, engineering branches and institutes. Specifically, experts will teach them how to choose the best engineering, pharmacy, or architecture colleges.The event will include lectures on science programmes, opportunities, research and national-level tests, etc.Management educationThe conference will also cover management education, particularly at the undergraduate level, and also opportunities for postgraduate management students and budding managers. Students can have a question-answer session with experts.Standards of higher education and the functions of statutory agencies such as the All India Council for Technical Education, Medical Council of India, Dental Council of India, Nursing Council of India, National Council for Teacher Education and Distance Education Council will also be highlighted.